The paper discusses methods for completing knowledge graphs, which is a common task in artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses embedding models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL), as it discusses methods for interpreting and evaluating information in knowledge graphs. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) as it discusses methods for predicting missing information in knowledge graphs.
